370 mL Black Beans
6 unit Flour Tortillas
160 g Sweet Bell Pepper
113 g Baby Tomatoes
113 g Yellow Onion
56 g Spring Mix
1 cup Monterey Jack Cheese, shredded
2 tbsp Tomato Sauce Base
2 tbsp Chipotle Sauce
1 tbsp Enchilada Spice Blend
1 tbsp Rice Vinegar
2.33 tbsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*
¼ tsp Sugar*

Before starting, preheat the oven to 450˚F.Wash and dry all produce. Core, then cut pepper into 1/4-inch pieces.Peel, then cut onion into 1/4-inch pieces.Halve tomatoes.

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high heat.When hot, add 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil, onions and 3/4 of the peppers. Cook, stirring occasionally, until softened and golden, 5-6 min.Meanwhile, using a strainer, drain and rinse black beans.Add black beans to a large bowl, then, using the back of a fork, lightly mash beans until they just burst.

Add Enchilada Spice Blend to veggies. Cook, stirring often, until fragrant, 30 sec.Remove pan from heat. Add tomato sauce base, chipotle sauce and black beans.Season with salt and pepper, then stir to combine.

Arrange tortillas on a clean surface.Using a spoon, divide bean mixture down the middle of each tortilla.Sprinkle half the cheese over top.Roll tortillas tightly over filling, then arrange them on a parchment-lined baking sheet, seam-side down.Brush taquitos with 1 tsp (2 tsp) oil, then sprinkle remaining cheese over top. Bake in the middle of the oven until golden-brown, 7-10 min.

Meanwhile, add vinegar, 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil, and 1/4 tsp (1/2 tsp) sugar to the same bowl used to mash black beans. Season with salt and pepper, then stir to combine.

Add tomatoes, spring mix and remaining peppers to bowl with dressing. Toss to coat.Divide taquitos and salad between plates.